FuncDef: This command defines the list of DS-0 timeslots to be used in the DS-1 or E-1 channel-group. The timeslots are defaulted as defined below when encap-type is setto/from atm. ATM channel groups do not allow timeslots to change.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the timeslot(s) to be associated with the channel group. The value can consist of a list of timeslots. Each member of the list can either be a single timeslot or a range of timeslots. Values-1 to 24 for DS-1 interfaces (the full range is auto-configured for ATM channel groups and cannot be changed)

2 to 32 for E-1 interfaces (the 2 to 16,18 to 32 ranges are auto-configured for ATM channel groups and cannot be changed).
